{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because it was, you know, you were only 20, 30 miles from your-- from your base, which in this case was in France.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "It was Luneville, France where we were based at that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We had left England, gone to France after D-day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they-- then they had scattered the Eighth and the Ninth Air Force, mostly the Ninth, all over in different places.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And this-- the Ninth Air Force was a medium-- we didn't have any heavy bombers, didn't have any B-17s.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The biggest airplanes we had were B-26s.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The twin engines and B-25s, twin engines, very fast, very, very powerful bombers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we flew escort missions with them too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But I mean targets were-- were opportunity.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Trains, convoys, troops if you could find them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We were-- we were train busters pretty much.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We-- when we killed a train, we got an engine painted on our fuselage, same as if you downed an ME-109, or a German fighter plane, or a bomber, any kind.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They would paint the kill on your-- on your fuselage of your airplane, on the nose of your airplane.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I'll show you some in there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "This, now we're getting into March of 19-- and oh, I was going to say.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "In 1944, in winter of '44, they sent-- the Ninth Air Force sent, I think it was two squadrons, which would have been 32 airplanes, to-- to Belgium.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And-- and-- and this was-- the Battle of the Bulge hadn't started, but it was safe, they thought, for us to be that close to where the combat.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "We were always 7 to 15 miles away, our fighter bases, from wherever the fight-- if it was static.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "If it was fluid, we were further back.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
